{"content": "Given \\( f(x) = x^7 + a x^3 + c x \\) and \\( f(5) = 3 \\), we are to find \\( f(-5) \\).\n\nFirst, write both expressions:\n\\[\nf(5) = 5^7 + a (5^3) + c(5) = 3\n\\]\n\\[\nf(-5) = (-5)^7 + a(-5^3) + c(-5)\n\\]\n\nLet's compute the relevant powers:\n\n- \\( 5^3 = 125 \\)\n- \\( 5^7 = (5^3)^2 \\cdot 5 = 125^2 \\cdot 5 = 15625 \\cdot 5 = 78125 \\)\n- \\( (-5)^3 = -125 \\)\n- \\( (-5)^7 = -(5^7) = -78125 \\)\n\nSo:\n\\[\nf(5) = 78125 + 125a + 5c = 3\n\\]\n\\[\nf(-5) = -78125 - 125a - 5c\n\\]\n\nNow, add \\( f(5) \\) and \\( f(-5) \\):\n\n\\[\nf(5) + f(-5) = [78125 + 125a + 5c] + [-78125 - 125a - 5c] = 0\n\\]\nSo,\n", "in": 150, "out": 300}